		<h3>Latest Owner Complaints About the Windstar</h3>
		<ul class="complaints latest">
			<li id="lc0" class="htrans">
	<h4><a href="/Ford/Windstar/2003/engine/dies_while_driving.shtml#8" title="2003 Ford Windstar: dies while driving on 19">dies while driving -- <span class="vehicle">2003 Windstar:</span></a></h4>
	<ul class="meta">
		<li><strong>Reported:</strong> February 19, 2012</li>
		<li><strong>Location:</strong> Coeburn, VA</li>
		<li><strong>Cost to Fix:</strong> Not Fixed</li>
	</ul>
	<p>The problem started last year about May we was driving down the road and it lost power and steering, brakes and everything went. Check engine light came on so took it to get checked and they said it was starter or alternator had both replaced. About a couple weeks later happens again and since ... <a href="/Ford/Windstar/2003/engine/dies_while_driving.shtml#8" title="dies while driving">Read more &raquo;</a></p>
	<p class="important">This problem has been <a href="/Ford/Windstar/2003/engine/dies_while_driving.shtml" title="2003 Ford Windstar: dies while driving on 19">reported 8 times by other 2003 Windstar owners</a>.</p>
